<br>
In Gemstone 3 there is a class that &quot;takes your wounds away.&quot;  I think it was called the empath.  Basically, not only do you take damage in terms of hit points but parts of your body get cuts scrapes bruises ... limb loss etc.    The empath can fix this &quot;beyond mere hitpoint damage.&quot;  By taking it on themselves and for that they get exp.  <br>
<br>
Empaths are brutally weak however and basically stayed in town (mostly chatting and healing people as I recall)  As you went up levels you could regenerate harder kinds of injuries up to raising the dead I think.  (Been a long time since I played a lot).  <br>
<br>
I always though that this was a great system to be integrated into healing as we do it... healing as the fight is ongoing....   It also integrated well into the economy.  Just a thought... has anyone seen anything like this in a MMoRPG or know of anything like it coming up. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dmitrythewizzy>Dmitry the Wizzy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/13/03 11:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kyron>Kyron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 12:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> SWG has a similiar feature implimented in 2 ways. Don't wanna say too much cause I am very tired and not sure whether the NDA covers that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13333<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 12:12 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> Necros have this ability now, or close enough. <p><a href="http://www.EQPixelArmy.com" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-animated-banner-animation.gif" height="120" width="80" alt="EQPA" border=0></a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41790" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-animated-banner-text.gif" height=120 width=272 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dmitrythewizzy>Dmitry the Wizzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>The People's Gnome</span><br>  Posts: 1871<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 12:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Necros have this ability now, or close enough.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Explain?<br>
<br>
Everquest does not have a &quot;wound and scar&quot; system and so there is no real equivilent.  <br>
<br>
I broke down and looked up the class in GS3:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.play.net/gs3/info/professions/empaths.asp">www.play.net/gs3/info/pro...mpaths.asp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
....for those who just popped in here to see if I was fighting with Rom and really don't wanna click... <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Empaths have the natural ability to transfer wounds from others to their own bodies. They then use their recuperative powers drawn from the spiritual realm of magic to heal themselves. They are rewarded by the gods and their patients as well for such selflessness. Their primary spells concentrate on self-healing, but they also have access to other spells more useful in combat. It is difficult, but not impossible for Empaths to gain skill in weapons and armor, though heavier armor types may adversely affect their ability to cast spells.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13339<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 2:58 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> Necros create mana by hurting themselves, and then can heal others over time using that mana. And both are spells that work over time, so you can have both going at once (and then add in a lifetap over time to be, essentially, moving the wounds off onto a third party).<br>
<br>
Not as direct as simply taking someone else's wounds onto themselves, but I suspect they could do that without too much trouble. It'd be an interesting variant spell for them, certainly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dmitrythewizzy>Dmitry the Wizzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>The People's Gnome</span><br>  Posts: 1885<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 10:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> That was half of the equation and I see what you mean now but the part that I actually thought was very clever was the &quot;wound&quot; system and how there was a class to deal with it.  <br>
<br>
If over time a player got nicks and cuts and banged up (there was also frozen limbs and electrical shock damage) you would slowly lose stats.  So not only do you have hit points but you have &quot;The ability to use your left arm is dimished because you have a slash across it.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Eventually, you would get so many of these bumps and bruises that you would need to see an empath (or use the appropriate herb/npc but that is another part of the scheme).  <br>
<br>
It forced players to participate in the &quot;town square.&quot;  Really social players who loved helping people played empaths.  They were always in demand and loved helping and got exp for it.  <br>
<br>
Anyway, I imagine many of you are in and about the development of games and I wanted to point out that this was one idea from a text mud that I had not seen appropriated yet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1365<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 10:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> Some people dont like item decay much - having to return to town to fix items that are degenerating over time in performance. You are basically describing item decay but for the player himself hehe.<br>
<br>
Interesting idea <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dmitrythewizzy>Dmitry the Wizzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>The People's Gnome</span><br>  Posts: 1887<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 11:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> Heh now that you mention it... I have posted that I like item decay.  I think I like it for the same reason I like &quot;player decay.&quot;  IE it forces centralized interraction of the player base.  <br>
<br>
I like player decay also because it would change the &quot;Raid Until you drop.&quot; dynamic a bit.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13275<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 12:21 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I like player decay also because it would change the &quot;Raid Until you drop.&quot; dynamic a bit.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->How? Guild empath sits in the Nexus with AFK on, people get sent to him as needed, and return to raiding. With guildhouses in EQ2, that'll just exacerbate it further -- no one will even see your 24/7 bot cluttering up the place. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fangarr>Fangarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 2:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> Actually, the best thing about Gemstone III, which is hidden within Dmitry's point, is that classes got XP for doing what they were good at.  Thieve's got xp for picking locks, Empaths got XP for taking wounds, etc, etc.   That is how they were able to stay in the city and offer such a service and still level without having to go kill mobs.  It gave every class a method of &quot;soloing&quot;.<br>
<br>
One of the problems with EQ is that you can boil down every class to how much damage it can do.  Clerics have Ice Comet caliber nukes these days in an effort to allow all classes to do damage because killing mobs is the only way to level.  In Gemstone there was no need for such things as you got XP for doing what you did best.<br>
<br>
