ld make sense, since I have a necro and have been a healer in groups. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dmitrythewizzy>Dmitry the Wizzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>The People's Gnome</span><br>  Posts: 1888<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 4:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> The empath was so fragile that it died if hit basically.  Remember, text muds have &quot;rooms&quot;  Mobs pop in the &quot;room&quot; in Gemstone... you could not avoid some random number generator popping a mob on your travelling empath at some point.  <br>
<br>
You are right though, graphical muds would need to dupicate this limitation to get the same &quot;socialization&quot; benefit.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 268<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 1:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> Well why you mention a necro's lich line of spells is beyond me then... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://people.ucsc.edu/~arice/pictures/zuratulisig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13311<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 2:47 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> Did you read the thread?<br>
<br>
Dmitry talked about a class that traded the PC's health into health for other PC's.<br>
<br>
Which is what lich + heal over time does, but in two steps, not one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1367<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 4:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Design element I liked from text muds...</span><hr size=1> I dont think Dmitry was talking about trading health from character to character, more (in EQ terms) trading a loss in *max* hp and max sta etc from one character to another. A character would get battle worn and his stats reduce until it would be too dangerous to fight any more since his max hp would reduce close to zero. That's why I compared this to item decay, where the stats slowly get worse and worse over time and are forced to be repaired.<br>
<br>
I also think that, seeing as most 'ubers' are not inclined towards item decay (they'd just see it as another pointless time sink as you described) they wouldnt appreciate player decay.<br>
<br>
